resource library 









Custom Plastic Manufacturing Capabilities
From our methods that range from prototyping to tooling to manufacturing, to our products which include open profile extrusion and complex micro-molding, Pexco has what it takes to bring your product to market, on-time and in-budget.




 Plastic Extrusion 


 Value Added Machining 


 Co-Extrusion 








Custom Plastics

Pexco was born in custom plastics. Specialty custom plastic solutions are part of Pexco’s DNA. We can serve your needs across countless market applications.
Learn More >





Methods
A spectrum of offerings
From extrusion to injection molding to custom machining and fabrication, Pexco has what you need. More than 100 engineering and production specialists provide consultation, design and production to meet a variety of end-use challenges. Services include product/part design and engineering, die development, production and other value-added services. 








Scalability
Continental footprint
In addition to our material and technology range, because of our geographic footprint we are also able to offer multiple points of manufacturing and the capacity to grow with you and your successes.









Materials
The difference is clear








Pexco is prepared with deep experience across a wide range of materials, from engineering resins such as Polycarbonate, Nylon, PEEK, Polysulfone, Pebax®, Polyetherimide (ULTEM®), PLA, Polyurethane and other elastomeric materials, to PVC, Acrylic, Polystyrene, and HDPE.  All together we process over 400 different materials and grades.



Fabrication
Precision to the end








Pexco offers the full range of post-process fabrication systems, allowing our customers to pare down the number of suppliers needed to produce a final part. Whether it’s assembly, packaging or machining, Pexco delivers on that ‘last touch’ your product deserves.





Quality Standards
Beyond industry standards








Pexco is FDA Registered, ITAR Compliant and certified to ISO 9001:2008, ISO 13485:2003 and also AS9100C.






















 




