Home /
Markets /
Medical





Medical Plastics Manfacturing
For 50+ years, medical companies have turned to Pexco for medical plastics. At Pexco you’ll find extensive development experience and a broad range of capabilities; financial stability and capacity across multiple sites; as well as our ability to maintain tight, repeatable outcomes when extruding, molding, CNC machining, and assembling components, medical devices, and surgical components.




 

 

 

 

 

 

 







Medical Products >

Pexco is a medical plastics manufacturer, specializing in premium injection molding, including high performance bioplastic and bioresorbable implants; advanced medical and surgical tubing and catheter components; and other profile extrusions. We provide a multitude of plastic component designs satisfying OEM customer needs. Below are the most common type of products we manufacture; however, our unique custom capabilities permit us to bring new solutions and applications each and every day.

Extruded Tubing

Single & Multilumen Tubing (up to 10 lumens depending on size)
Microbore & Catheter Tubing (min OD 0.0025"; min ID .0018")
Surgical Tubing
Co- and Tri-Extrusions
Paratubing
Wire-reinforced or braided Tubing 


Injection molding

Medical Devices Injection Molding
Surgical Implantable components and kits
Bioresorbable materials
Micromolding
Insert Molding
Multishot Molding
Packaged assemblies




Additional Extrusion, Injection Molding, and Other Profiles

Custom Medical Plastics





A Continental Footprint
With over eight medical Class 7 and Class 8 clean rooms across 5 sites in North America, including 2 in Mexico, Pexco has your manufacturing needs covered, with the capacity to grow with your products’ launch and success. View More > 








 Five sites across the four corners of medical manufacturing at Pexco, "quint"essentially covering every major medical plastics region in North America.





